---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
const updated = 'May 3, 2026';
---
<Base
  title="Privacy Policy — RangeDOPE"
  description="RangeDOPE privacy policy. We collect minimal data and never sell it."
>

<style>
  nav {
    position: fixed; top: 0; left: 0; right: 0; z-index: 100;
    display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: space-between;
    padding: 16px clamp(20px, 5vw, 60px);
    background: rgba(8,8,8,0.9);
    backdrop-filter: blur(16px);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
  }
  .nav-brand { display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 10px; opacity: 1; }
  .nav-logo { width: 28px; height: 28px; border-radius: 7px; }
  .nav-name {
    font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 13px; font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: 2px; color: var(--label);
  }
  .nav-name span { color: var(--primary); }
  .back-link {
    font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 10px; letter-spacing: 1.5px;
    color: var(--dim); text-transform: uppercase;
  }
  .back-link:hover { color: var(--primary); opacity: 1; }

  .page {
    max-width: 720px; margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 120px clamp(20px, 5vw, 40px) 80px;
  }

  /* Header */
  .page-header { margin-bottom: 56px; }
  .page-label {
    font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 10px; letter-spacing: 3px;
    color: var(--primary); text-transform: uppercase; margin-bottom: 16px;
    display: block;
  }
  h1 {
    font-size: clamp(32px, 5vw, 52px); font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: -1.5px; color: var(--white); margin-bottom: 16px;
  }
  .meta {
    font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 11px; letter-spacing: 1px;
    color: var(--dim);
  }

  /* Sections */
  section { margin-bottom: 48px; }
  h2 {
    font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 10px; letter-spacing: 3px;
    text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--primary);
    margin-bottom: 16px; padding-bottom: 10px;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
  }
  p { font-size: 15px; color: #b0b0b0; line-height: 1.85; margin-bottom: 14px; }
  ul { padding-left: 20px; margin-bottom: 14px; }
  li { font-size: 15px; color: #b0b0b0; line-height: 1.85; margin-bottom: 6px; }
  strong { color: var(--label); font-weight: 600; }
  a { color: var(--primary); }
  a:hover { opacity: 0.8; }

  .tag {
    display: inline-block;
    font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 9px; letter-spacing: 1.5px;
    color: var(--primary); background: var(--primary-g);
    border: 1px solid rgba(255,48,0,0.2); border-radius: 4px;
    padding: 3px 8px; margin: 0 4px 4px 0;
  }

  .contact-card {
    background: var(--surface); border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: var(--radius-md); padding: 24px 28px; margin-top: 12px;
  }
  .contact-card p { margin: 0; font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 13px; }

  footer {
    border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
    padding: 32px clamp(20px, 5vw, 60px);
    display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: space-between; flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: 16px;
  }
  .footer-copy { font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 10px; color: var(--dim2); }
  .footer-home { font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 10px; color: var(--dim); letter-spacing: 1px; text-transform: uppercase; }
  .footer-home:hover { color: var(--primary); opacity: 1; }
</style>

<!-- Nav -->
<nav>
  <a href="/" class="nav-brand">
    <img src="/logo.png" alt="RangeDOPE" class="nav-logo" />
    <span class="nav-name">Range<span>DOPE</span></span>
  </a>
  <a href="/" class="back-link">← Back to Home</a>
</nav>

<main class="page">
  <header class="page-header">
    <span class="page-label">Legal</span>
    <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p class="meta">Effective: {updated} &nbsp;·&nbsp; Last updated: {updated}</p>
  </header>

  <section>
    <h2>Overview</h2>
    <p>
      RangeDOPE ("the App") is a long-range ballistic solver and hunt planning tool for iOS.
      This policy describes what information we collect, why we collect it, and how it is used.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>The short version:</strong> we collect as little as possible, we don't sell your data,
      and your hunting spots stay on your phone.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Information We Collect</h2>

    <p><strong>Location Data <span class="tag">WHEN IN USE ONLY</span></strong></p>
    <p>
      The App requests access to your device location for two purposes only:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>Auto-filling shooter position (latitude, longitude, elevation) in the Shot Plan screen</li>
      <li>Fetching local atmospheric data (temperature, pressure, humidity) for ballistic corrections</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      <strong>Your location is processed on-device and is never transmitted to our servers or shared
      with any third party.</strong> We do not collect or store location history. Location access
      is optional — all coordinates can be entered manually.
    </p>

    <p><strong>Hunt Waypoints & Shot Plans</strong></p>
    <p>
      Waypoints, sightings, stands, glassing points, and shot plan data you create are stored
      locally on your device using iOS's built-in secure storage. This data is never uploaded
      to any server and is never accessible to us.
    </p>

    <p><strong>Purchases & Subscriptions <span class="tag">REVENUECAT</span></strong></p>
    <p>
      In-app purchases are processed by Apple through the App Store. We use
      <a href="https://www.revenuecat.com/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener">RevenueCat</a>
      to manage subscription entitlements. RevenueCat may collect a pseudonymous device identifier
      for entitlement verification. No payment information is processed by us directly.
      See <a href="https://www.revenuecat.com/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener">RevenueCat's Privacy Policy</a>
      and <a href="https://www.apple.com/legal/privacy/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Apple's Privacy Policy</a>.
    </p>

    <p><strong>Map Tiles</strong></p>
    <p>
      Map tiles are loaded from third-party services including USGS National Map, ESRI World
      Imagery, and the BLM Surface Management Agency. These are standard tile requests that
      include your map viewport bounding box — consistent with any mapping application. We do
      not control or store this data.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>What We Do NOT Collect</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Your name, email address, or any account information</li>
      <li>Background location or location history</li>
      <li>Device contacts, photos, or camera</li>
      <li>Advertising identifiers (no ad SDKs)</li>
      <li>Crash analytics or usage telemetry (no Firebase, Amplitude, Mixpanel, etc.)</li>
      <li>Your rifle profiles, load data, or DOPE cards</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Data Retention & Deletion</h2>
    <p>
      All app data — rifle profiles, shot plans, waypoints, DOPE cards — is stored locally
      on your device. <strong>Deleting the App removes all locally stored data permanently.</strong>
    </p>
    <p>
      RevenueCat retains purchase records to restore entitlements. Contact
      <a href="https://www.revenuecat.com/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener">RevenueCat</a>
      directly for deletion requests related to their records.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Children</h2>
    <p>
      RangeDOPE is not directed at children under 17. We do not knowingly collect any
      information from minors. The App is rated 17+ on the App Store.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Changes to This Policy</h2>
    <p>
      If we make material changes we will update the "Last Updated" date above. Continued use
      of the App after changes constitutes acceptance of the updated policy.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Contact</h2>
    <p>Questions or concerns about your privacy? We're a one-person shop — reach out directly:</p>
    <div class="contact-card">
      <p>
        RangeDOPE Support<br />
        <a href="mailto:mike@techridgeseo.com">mike@techridgeseo.com</a>
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</main>

<footer>
  <span class="footer-copy">© {new Date().getFullYear()} RangeDOPE. All rights reserved.</span>
  <a href="/" class="footer-home">← getrangedope.com</a>
</footer>

</Base>
